The package tgfx provides CMake targets:

    find_package(tgfx CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE tgfx::tgfx)

Available features:
- svg: Enable building the SVG module
- layers: Enable building the layers module
- qt: Enable building with the Qt framework
- swiftshader: Enable building with the SwiftShader library
- angle: Enable building with the ANGLE library
- async-promise: Enable async promises for loading images on the web

Example usage with features:
vcpkg install "tgfx[svg,layers]"

For HarmonyOS platform support:
1. Set OHOS_NDK_HOME environment variable to your HarmonyOS NDK path
2. Use overlay-triplets to include the custom HarmonyOS triplets
3. Available triplets:
   - x64-ohos: for x86_64 architecture
   - arm64-ohos: for ARM64 architecture
   - arm-ohos: for ARM v7a architecture

Example usage for HarmonyOS:
    vcpkg install tgfx:x64-ohos --overlay-triplets=triplets
    vcpkg install tgfx:arm64-ohos --overlay-triplets=triplets
    vcpkg install tgfx:arm-ohos --overlay-triplets=triplets

Note: The triplets directory should contain the custom HarmonyOS triplet files.
